  "prompt": "What is the temperature on the planet Mercury at the demarcation point between light and dark?",
  "response": "The temperature on Mercury varies significantly between its sunlit side and its dark side due to its slow rotation and lack of atmosphere. At the demarcation point, or terminator (the dividing line between the light and dark sides), temperatures can be quite extreme. \n\nOn the sunlit side, temperatures can reach around 430 degrees Celsius (about 800 degrees Fahrenheit), while on the dark side, temperatures can drop to about -180 degrees Celsius (approximately -290 degrees Fahrenheit). The temperature at the terminator can be somewhat intermediate, but it is often estimated to be in the range of -20 to -40 degrees Celsius (-4 to -40 degrees Fahrenheit). \n\nThese values can vary, but the key takeaway is that the terminator region experiences a stark temperature contrast, influenced by the lack of atmosphere to moderate these extremes.",
